Spec: SpecDD Adopt Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in creating, restructuring, or improving target-project `.sdd` specs without implementation work unless explicitly requested.

Owns:
  ./specdd-adopt/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-adopt/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Resolve target project bootstrap files and governing specs before spec edits.
  Treat the user's request as target scope, not as permission to bypass active authority.
  Read existing ancestor specs for the target area before adding new specs.
  Identify the smallest useful spec boundary for the requested adoption work.
  Prefer a root or nearest-area spec before adding narrow child specs.
  Use path-based ownership, explicit `References`, and `Can modify` or `Owns` to make scope and write authority discoverable.
  Keep created specs concise, local, behavioral, and authority-oriented.
  Include only sections that add useful local authority, constraints, behavior, tasks, or context.
  Report bootstrap files read, specs created or changed, intended governing scope, and unresolved adoption decisions.

Must not:
  Change implementation files unless explicitly requested.
  Copy SpecDD framework rules into target project specs.
  Imply authority from similar names, nearby files, symbols, or observations.
  Turn uncertain observations into durable contracts.
  Edit when write authority, ownership, public behavior, or security scope is unclear.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
